Good idea. I&#x27;ll add &quot;fetch files from other domains&quot; to the TODO list, as either it&#x27;s own call, or maybe do something like allowing &quot;<a href="http://&quot;" rel="nofollow">http://&quot;</a> protocols in the SLFSRV.read() method.<p>cross-origin issues would probably prevent some xmlhttprequest calls directly. Meanwhile, here is one current hack you could use to read files from other domains (although it assumes that &quot;curl&quot; is installed):<p>SLFSRV.exec( { program:&#x27;curl&#x27;, args:[&#x27;curl&#x27;,&#x27;<a href="https://news.ycombinator.com/&#x27;" rel="nofollow">https://news.ycombinator.com/&#x27;</a>] },
             function(ret) {
                 console.log(ret.stdout);
            }
);
